parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Rear Wheel Well Plate Affecting Rear Seat Belt Anchor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the rear wheel well plate can cause the rear seat belt anchor to break free, rendering the rear seat belts useless, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Rear seat belts are loose or not functioning properly
noise or rattling from the rear wheel well area
signs of corrosion or rust on the rear wheel well plate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt does not retract properly
seat belt is loose or not functioning properly
noise or clicking sound from the seat belt retractor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rusting of Rear Seat Belt Mounts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusting of the rear seat belt mounts can cause the mounts to break, rendering the rear seat belts useless, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Rear seat belts are loose or not functioning properly
signs of rust or corrosion on the rear seat belt mounts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailability of Parts for Seat Belt Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unavailability of parts for seat belt recall repair can leave vehicles with defective seat belts on the road, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealer unable to repair seat belt due to unavailability of parts
recall notice received but repair cannot be completed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Seat Belt Failure Causing Injury
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of Takata seat belts can cause injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt failed to restrain occupant during an accident
injury or fatality occurred as a result of seat belt failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire tread is peeling away from the tire
